     section
         h2 About transitions
         br
         p There are three categories of unique transitions to choose from, all of which can be found on the Transitions tab:
           li Subtle: These are the most basic types of transitions. They use simple animations to move between slides.
    
     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/trans/tran1.png")
     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         p Exciting: These use more complex animations to transition between slides. While they're more visually interesting than Subtle transitions, adding too many can make your presentation look less professional. However, when used in moderation they can add an nice touch between important slides.
    
     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/trans/tran2.png")

     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         p Dynamic Content: If you're transitioning between two slides that use similar slide layouts, dynamic transitions will move only the placeholders, not the slides themselves. When used correctly, dynamic transitions can help to unify your slides and add a further level of polish to your presentation.
  
     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/trans/tran3.png")
  
     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To apply a transition:
         p
           li Select the desired slide from the Slide Navigation pane. This is the slide that will appear after the transition.
         img(src="images/trans/tran4.jpg")

     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click the Transitions tab, then locate the Transition to This Slide group. By default, None is applied to each slide.
         li Click the More drop-down arrow to display all transitions.
         img(src="images/trans/tran5.png")

    section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click a transition to apply it to the selected slide. This will automatically preview the transition.
         img(src="images/trans/tran6.png") 

     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li You can use the Apply To All command in the Timing group to apply the same transition to all slides in your presentation. Keep in mind that this will modify any other transitions you've applied.
         img(src="images/trans/tran7.png")

     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To preview a transition:
         p
            li Click the Preview command on the Transitions tab.
         img(src="images/trans/tran.png")

     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click the Play Animations command in the Slide Navigation pane.
         img(src="images/trans/tran8.jpg")

     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To modify the transition effect:
         p
           li Select the slide with the transition you wish to modify.
           li Click the Effect Options command, and choose the desired option. These options will vary depending on the selected transition.
           li The transition will be modified, and a preview of the transition will appear.

     section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/trans/tran9.png")
    
