      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li To rename the section, click the Section command, then choose Rename Section from the drop-down menu.
        img(src="images/manage/manage11.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Type the new section name in the dialog box, then click Rename.
        img(src="images/manage/manage12.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Repeat to add as many sections as you need.
        li In the slide navigation pane, click the arrow next to a section name to collapse or expand it.
        img(src="images/manage/manage13.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li To remove a section, click the Section command, then click Remove Section. You can also click Remove All Sections to remove all sections from your slides.
        img(src="images/manage/manage14.png")
      
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h2 Print Layouts
        p  PowerPoint includes several different layouts when printing a presentation. The layout you choose will mostly depend on why you're printing the slide show. There are four different print layouts:
    
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Full-page slides: This prints a full page for each slide in your presentation. This layout would be most useful if you needed to review or edit a printed copy of your presentation.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/printing/print_layout_slide.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Notes: This prints each slide, along with any speaker notes for the slide. If you've included a lot of notes for each slide, you could keep a printed copy of the notes with you while presenting.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/printing/print_layout_notes.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Outline: This prints an overall outline of the slide show. You could use this layout to review the organization of your slide show and prepare to deliver your presentation. 

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/printing/print_layout_outlineB.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Handouts: This prints thumbnail versions of each slide, with optional space for notes. This layout is especially useful if you want to give your audience a physical copy of the presentation. The optional space allows them to take notes on each slide.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/printing/print_layout_handouts.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To access the print pane
         li Select the File tab. Backstage view will appear.
         img(src="images/printing/know_backstage_file.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Select Print. The Print pane will appear.
         img(src="images/printing/print_backstage_click.png")
 
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click the buttons in the interactive below to learn more about using the Print pane.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/printing/BACKGROUND.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li You can also access the Print pane by pressing Ctrl+P on your keyboard.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To print a presentation:
         li Select the File tab. Backstage view will appear.
         img(src="images/printing/know_backstage_file(1).png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Select Print. The Print pane will appear.
         img(src="images/printing/print_backstage_click(1).png")
   
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Choose the desired printer and print range.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Chose the desired print layout and color settings.
         img(src="images/printing/print_command_printer_color.png")
      
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li When you're done modifying the settings, click Print.
         img(src="images/printing/print_command.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 Presenting a slide show
         p Click the Start From Beginning command on the Quick Access toolbar, or press the F5 key at the top of your keyboard. The presentation will appear in full-screen mode.
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
      img(src="images/present slide/command.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li You can also click the Play Slide Show command at the bottom of the PowerPoint window to begin a presentation from the current slide.
         img(src="images/present slide/command1.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click the Slide Show tab on the Ribbon to access even more options. From here, you can start the presentation from the current slide and access advanced presentation options.
      img(src="images/present slide/splat.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 To stop a slide show :
         p You can exit presentation mode by clicking the Esc key on your keyboard. Alternatively, you can click the Slide Show Options button in the bottom-left and then select End Show.
         img(src="images/present slide/command2.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li The presentation will also end after the last slide. You can click the mouse or press the space bar to return to Normal view.
         img(src="images/present slide/command3.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 To access drawing tools:
         p Your mouse pointer can act as pen or highlighter to draw attention to items in your slides.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Locate and select the Pen Tools button in the bottom-left corner.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Select Pen or Highlighter based on your preference.
      img(src="images/present slide/command4.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click and drag the mouse to mark your slides. You can also press Ctrl+P on your keyboard to access the pen tool while presenting your slide show.
      img(src="images/present slide/mark.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 To show the taskbar:
         p Sometimes you may need to access the Internet or other files and programs on your computer during your presentation. PowerPoint allows you to access your taskbar without ending the presentation.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Locate and select the Slide Options button in the bottom-left corner.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Select Screen, then click Show Taskbar.
         img(src="images/present slide/taskbar1.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Your taskbar will appear. Choose a program you'd like to open, such as a web browser. Click the PowerPoint icon to return to the presentation.
         img(src="images/present slide/nograde.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 Slide options
         p You can also access any of the menu items above by right-clicking anywhere on the screen during your slide show.
         img(src="images/present slide/click.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 To access slide show setup options:

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Select the Slide Show tab, then click the Set Up Slide Show command.
         img(src="images/present slide/command5.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Click the buttons in the interactive below to learn about various options for setting up and playing a slide show.
         img(src="images/present slide/background.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li To advance slides automatically, you'll need to customize the slide timing on the Transitions tab. Review our lesson on Applying Transitions to learn how.
         img(src="images/present slide/automatic.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h1 Lists
      
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To modify the bullet style:
         p
           li Select an existing list you want to format.
           li On the Home tab, click the Bullets drop-down arrow.
         img(src="images/list/l1.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Select the desired bullet style from the menu that appears.
         img(src="images/list/l2.png")
         li The bullet style will appear in the list.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          h3 To modify a numbered list:
          p
            li Select an existing list you want to format.
            li On the Home tab, click the Numbering drop-down arrow.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li Select the desired numbering option from the menu that appears.
           img(src="images/list/l3.png")
          li The numbering option will appear in the list.
     
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          h3 To change the starting number:
          p
             li Select an existing numbered list.
             li On the Home tab, click the Numbering drop-down arrow.
   
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li Select Bullets and Numbering from the menu that appears.
          img(src="images/list/l4.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li A dialog box will appear. In the Start At field, enter the desired starting numbert
          img(src="images/list/l5.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
          li The list numbering will change.
          img(src="images/list/l6.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To indent text:
        li Indenting helps to format the layout of text so it appears more organized on your slide. The fastest way to indent is to use the Tab key. An alternative method of creating an indent is to use one of the Indent commands. With these commands, you can either increase or decrease the indent.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li To indent using the Tab key: Place the insertion point at the very beginning of the line you want to indent, then press the Tab key.
        img(src="images/indent/indent1.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li To indent using the Indent commands: Place the insertion point at the very beginning of the line you you want to indent.
        img(src="images/indent/indent2.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 Indenting lists and paragraphs
        li Indenting will give different results, depending upon whether you are working with a list or a paragraph:

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li List: Indenting a line of a list creates a multilevel list. This means the indented line is a subtopic of the line above it. Multilevel lists are useful if you want to create an outline or hierarchy.
        img(src="images/indent/indent3.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Paragraph: Indenting the first line of a paragraph using the Tab key creates a first-line indent. This helps to separate paragraphs from each other.
        img(src="images/indent/indent4.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Once you've created a multilevel list, you may wish to choose a different bullet style for different levels of the list to make them stand out even more.
        img(src="images/indent/indent5.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To show the ruler:
        li Select the View tab on the Ribbon.
        li In the Show group, check the box next to Ruler. The ruler will appear.
        img(src="images/indent/indent6.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 Indent markers
        li Indent markers are located to the left of the horizontal ruler, and they provide several indenting options:
        li First-line indent marker Bar Tab Icon: Adjusts the first line of a paragraph
        li Hanging indent marker Bar Tab Icon: Adjusts every line of a paragraph except for the first line

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Left indent marker Bar Tab Icon: Moves both the first-line indent and hanging indent markers at the same time; this will indent all lines in a paragraph
        img(src="images/indent/indent7.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To indent using the indent markers:
        li Place the insertion point anywhere in the paragraph where you wish to indent, or select one or more paragraphs.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Click, hold, and drag the desired indent marker. In our example, we'll drag the hanging indent marker.
        img(src="images/indent/indent8.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Release the mouse. The paragraph will be indented.
        img(src="images/indent/indent9.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h2 Line spacing
        li PowerPoint allows you to adjust the amount of space between each line in a list or paragraph. You can reduce the line spacing to fit more lines on a slide, or you can increase it to improve readability. In some instances, PowerPoint may automatically change the font size when you adjust the line spacing, so increasing the line spacing too much may cause the text to be too small.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To format line spacing:
        li Select the text you want to format.
        li On the Home tab, locate the Paragraph group, then click the Line Spacing command.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Select the desired line spacing from the menu that appears.
        img(src="images/indent/indent10.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li If you want to adjust the line spacing with even more precision, select Line Spacing Options from the drop-down menu.
        img(src="images/indent/indent11.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h2 Inserting Pictures
        h3 To insert a picture from a file:
        li Select the Insert tab, then click the Pictures command in the Images group.
        img(src="images/picture/picture_insert_command.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li A dialog box will appear. Locate and select the desired image file, then click Insert.
        img(src="images/picture/picture_insert_fruit.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li The picture will appear on the currently selected slide.
        img(src="images/picture/picture_insert_done.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li You can also click the Pictures command in a placeholder to insert images.
        img(src="images/picture/picture_insert_splat.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        p If you don't have the picture you want on your computer, you can find a picture online to add to your presentation. PowerPoint offers two options for finding online pictures:
        li OneDrive: You can insert an image stored on your OneDrive (previously called SkyDrive). You can also link other online accounts with your Microsoft account, such as Facebook or Flickr.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/picture/2015_picture_onedrive.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Bing Image Search: You can use this option to search the Internet for images. By default, Bing only shows images that are licensed under Creative Commons, which means you can use them for your own projects. However, you should go to the image's website to see if there are any restrictions on how it can be used.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/picture/picture_online_bing.png") 

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To insert an online picture:
        li Select the Insert tab, then click the Online Pictures command.
        img(src="images/picture/picture_online_command.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li The Insert Pictures dialog box will appear.
        li Choose Bing Image Search or your OneDrive. In our example, we'll use Bing Image Search.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/picture/2015_images_search.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li Press the Enter key. Your search results will appear in the dialog box.
        li Select the desired image, then click Insert.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/picture/picture_online_insert.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        li The image will appear on the currently selected slide.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/picture/picture_online_insert_big.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h2 Moving and resizing pictures
        p Once you've inserted a picture, you may want to move it to a different location on the slide or change its size. PowerPoint makes it easy to arrange pictures in your presentation.
        h3 To select a picture:

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        p Before you can modify a picture, you'll need to select it.
        li Simply click to select a picture. A solid line will appear around a selected picture.

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        img(src="images/picture/picture_move_select.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To resize a picture:
        li Click and drag the corner sizing handles until the picture is the desired size.
        img(src="images/picture/picture_move_resize.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To rotate a picture:
        li Click and drag the arrow above an image to rotate it right or left.
        img(src="images/picture/picture_move_rotate.png")

      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
        h3 To move a picture:
        li Click and drag to move a picture to a new location on a slide.
        img(src="images/picture/picture_move_move.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To delete a picture:
         li Select the picture you wish to delete, then press the Backspace or Delete key on your keyboard.
         img(src="images/picture/picture_format.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h2 Inserting screenshots
         p Screenshots are basically just snapshots of your computer screen. You can take a screenshot of almost any program, website, or open window. PowerPoint makes it easy to insert a screenshot of an entire window or a screen clipping of part of a window in your presentation.
         h3 To insert screenshots of a window:

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li Select the Insert tab, then click the Screenshot command in the Images group.
         li The Available Windows from your desktop will appear. Select the window you would like to capture as a screenshot.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/picture/picture_screenshot_command.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li The screenshot will appear on the currently selected slide.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/picture/picture_screenshot_done.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         h3 To insert a screen clipping:
         li Select the Insert tab, click the Screenshot command, then select Screen Clipping.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/picture/picture_clip_command.png")

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li A faded view of your desktop will appear. Click and drag to draw the area you want to capture as a screen clipping.

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/picture/picture_clip_draw.png"

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         li The screen clipping will appear on the currently selected slide

       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')
         img(src="images/picture/picture_screenshot_done.png")
         







